description: Describes a version of an Amazon Lookout for Vision model. This operation requires permissions to perform the lookoutvision:DescribeModel operation.

parameters.name: ProjectName
parameters.description: The project that contains the version of a model that you want to describe.

parameters.name: ModelVersion
parameters.description: The version of the model that you want to describe.

nested_items.name: ModelDescription
nested_items.description: Contains the description of the model.

nested_items.name: ModelVersion
nested_items.description: The version of the model.

nested_items.name: ModelArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the model.

nested_items.name: CreationTimestamp
nested_items.description: The unix timestamp for the date and time that the model was created.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: The description for the model.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The status of the model.

nested_items.name: StatusMessage
nested_items.description: The status message for the model.

nested_items.name: Performance
nested_items.description: Performance metrics for the model. Created during training.

nested_items.name: F1Score
nested_items.description: The overall F1 score metric for the trained model.

nested_items.name: Recall
nested_items.description: The overall recall metric value for the trained model.

nested_items.name: Precision
nested_items.description: The overall precision metric value for the trained model.

nested_items.name: OutputConfig
nested_items.description: The S3 location where Amazon Lookout for Vision saves model training files.

nested_items.name: S3Location
nested_items.description: The S3 location for the output.

nested_items.name: Bucket
nested_items.description: The S3 bucket that contains the training or model packaging job output. If you are training a model, the bucket must in your AWS account. If you use an S3 bucket for a model packaging job, the S3 bucket must be in the same AWS Region and AWS account in which you use AWS IoT Greengrass.

nested_items.name: Prefix
nested_items.description: The path of the folder, within the S3 bucket, that contains the output.

nested_items.name: EvaluationManifest
nested_items.description: The S3 location where Amazon Lookout for Vision saves the manifest file that was used to test the trained model and generate the performance scores.

nested_items.name: Bucket
nested_items.description: The bucket that contains the training output.

nested_items.name: Key
nested_items.description: The location of the training output in the bucket.

nested_items.name: EvaluationResult
nested_items.description: The S3 location where Amazon Lookout for Vision saves the performance metrics.

nested_items.name: Bucket
nested_items.description: The bucket that contains the training output.

nested_items.name: Key
nested_items.description: The location of the training output in the bucket.

nested_items.name: EvaluationEndTimestamp
nested_items.description: The unix timestamp for the date and time that the evaluation ended.

nested_items.name: KmsKeyId
nested_items.description: The identifer for the AWS Key Management Service (AWS KMS) key that was used to encrypt the model during training.

nested_items.name: MinInferenceUnits
nested_items.description: The minimum number of inference units used by the model. For more information, see  StartModel.

nested_items.name: MaxInferenceUnits
nested_items.description: The maximum number of inference units Amazon Lookout for Vision uses to auto-scale the model. For more information, see  StartModel.
